=80=99s like, let=E2=80=99s let the local community figure this out.=E2=80=
=9D New Hampshire Senator <strong>Jeanne Shaheen</strong> had roughly the s=
ame response, saying, =E2=80=9CWe can police it through the organizations.=
=E2=80=9D Axios reported that Wisconsin Senator <strong>Tammy Baldwin</stro=
ng>, the first openly gay member of the U.S. Senate, organized the messagin=
g push=E2=80=94just as Senate Dems successfully
filibustered a G.O.P.-backed bill to ban federally funded schools from allo=
wing transgender athletes to participate in women=E2=80=99s sports. =E2=80=
=9CRepublicans in Washington are saying they know better than parents and l=
ocal school districts,=E2=80=9D Baldwin told Axios. =E2=80=9CThey are wrong=
=2E I trust parents, schools, and local=
 sports leagues to make these decision=
s for their children.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=
=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">All of these comments ar=
