"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">Plenty of
Democrats=E2=80=94and plenty of Newsom=E2=80=99s critics in recent days=E2=
=80=94engage in a nifty bit of misdirection by claiming this is all a fake =
wedge issue invented by Republicans. Pretending it=E2=80=99s a non-issue is=
 unfair, not only to opponents of trans sports participation, but also to y=
oung trans athletes and their families. Progressives frequently cite NCAA p=
resident <strong>Charlie Baker</strong>, who said last year that there are =
=E2=80=9Cless than 10=E2=80=9D transgender athletes participating in colleg=
e sports. But this isn=E2=80=99t
just about college sports. The Williams Institute at UCLA Law School estima=
tes that =E2=80=9Cas many as 122,000 transgender youth could be participati=
ng in high school=E2=80=93level team athletics.=E2=80=9D That may not be a =
