reak:break-word;"><tbody><tr><td style=3D"padding-bottom:32px;"><div style=
=3D"color:#000000;direction:ltr;font-family:&#39;Inter&#39;,&#39;Arial&#39;=
;font-size:17px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:0px;line-height:150%;text-al=
ign:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0p=
x;">Democrats were emphatically less okay with comments like Newsom=E2=80=
=99s before last November=E2=80=99s
electoral drubbing, or even in the weeks after. At the time, many strategis=
ts and plenty of electeds were speaking out against the loud activists and =
identity groups that, they claimed, had dragged the party far left, outside=
 the mainstream sensibilities of working-class voters and swingy suburbanit=
es. =E2=80=9CDemocrats spend way too much time trying not to offend anyone =
rather than being brutally honest about the challenges many Americans face,=
=E2=80=9D Massachusetts Congressman <strong>Seth Moulton</strong>
told <em>The New York Times</em> just days after the November election. =E2=
=80=9CI have two little girls. I don=E2=80=99t want them getting run over o=
n a playing field by a male or formerly male athlete, but as a Democrat I=
=E2=80=99m supposed to be afraid to say that.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p><p style=3D=
"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:=
0px;">After those comments went live, Moulton faced demonstrations at his o=
ffice and was pilloried by local LGBTQ activists, plenty of local Democrati=
c officials,
the Massachusetts Democratic Party chairman, and even Gov. <strong>Maura He=
aley</strong>, who said Moulton was =E2=80=9Cplaying politics with people.=
=E2=80=9D I called Moulton on Tuesday, four months after he was in the barr=
el, to get his perspective on Newsom=E2=80=99s comments. Moulton said he wa=
s pleased that Democrats mostly weren=E2=80=99t condemning Newsom, and told=
 me it demonstrates that Democrats have the <em>potential</em> at least to =
have conversations about uncomfortable topics.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:=
0;
margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=E2=
=80=9CWe are not going to be a majority party if we can=E2=80=99t accept po=
ints of view from the majority of Americans,=E2=80=9D Moulton told me. =E2=
=80=9CDems need to get real, and it=E2=80=99s encouraging to see other Demo=
crats do just that. We are making progress, because the backlash, although =
still bad, is far less than what I saw four months ago.=E2=80=9D Moulton al=
so told me that when he got back to Capitol Hill after last November=E2=80=
=99s election, dozens of Democratic
members thanked him for speaking out=E2=80=94but they felt the need to whis=
per their compliments so no one would overhear.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;mar=
gin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">But bac=
k to my perfectly coiffed governor for a moment. Newsom may or may not run =
for president=E2=80=94and I think more people should consider the possibili=
ty that he may <em>not</em>, and that this podcast journey is just Newsom i=
n late-career D.G.A.F. mode with his party at rock bottom. Whatever he
chooses, this whole episode made for a fascinating test case of what=E2=80=
=99s to come if Democrats actually follow through on what needs to be done,=
 in format and message, before the 2028 election. Here was Newsom doing <em=
>precisely</em> what smarty-pants Democrats strategists were calling for in=
 the wake of the November election. Breaking with the left on an unpopular =
issue? <em>Check. </em>Engaging with voices outside the blue cultural bubbl=
e? <em>Check. </em>Experimenting with new media channels
that have become dominated by right-wing voices? <em>Check.</em></p><p styl=
e=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bot=
tom:0px;">None of it was perfect. Newsom=E2=80=99s loose delivery probably =
wasn=E2=80=99t ideal=E2=80=94=E2=80=9CRight position, wrong everything else=
,=E2=80=9D one plugged-in California Dem told me. He could have more fully =
explained a larger policy framework or political view on trans youth. If he=
=E2=80=99s opposed to trans girls and women playing in youth and college sp=
orts, then why did he not
speak out on the issue until now? Is he backtracking on all the other trans=
 protections he=E2=80=99s supported in the past? Would he support a trans s=
ports ban, but simultaneously defend trans rights on healthcare, housing di=
scrimination, legal name changes, bathroom access, or anything else?=C2=A0<=
/p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;=
margin-bottom:0px;">If Newsom <em>does</em> want to crack down on trans you=
th in girls sports, there is literally a Republican bill in
the California Assembly=E2=80=94The Protect Girls=E2=80=99 Sports Act=E2=80=
=94that he could endorse right now. But of course, he won=E2=80=99t. Maybe =
Newsom will clarify some of these questions in a future sit-down with a mem=
ber of the press. But I doubt he=E2=80=99ll do that, either. Despite his sm=
ooth-talker reputation, Newsom can be pretty uncomfortable around hungry re=
porters in unscripted settings. Which is one reason, I suspect, that he=E2=
=80=99s decided to host his own podcast.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bot=
tom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">As for his performance, Newsom w=
as probably a little too solicitous of Kirk in his maiden podcasting voyage=
, playing the role of a glib morning show host and forgetting, perhaps, tha=
t he=E2=80=99s first and foremost a Democrat=E2=80=94a leader with a lot of=
 Democratic followers who wanted him to take a scalpel to the cocky Turning=
 Point founder, not get chummy with a patron saint of MAGA. Engaging with a=
 political opponent in a longform, non-hostile format=E2=80=94the stated mi=
ssion of Newsom=E2=80=99s
podcast=E2=80=94is truly rare in today=E2=80=99s divided media landscape, a=
nd it=E2=80=99s honestly refreshing at a time when partisans rarely engage =
with people outside their ideological cocoons and voters shield themselves =
from discourse they don=E2=80=99t like. But Newsom, as one seasoned Democra=
tic strategist put it to me, sounded like he was interviewing Kirk for an e=
pisode of <em>How I Built This</em>. Media people might be into it, but in =
the mind=E2=80=99s eye of a progressive, Kirk is still The Enemy.=C2=A0</p>=
</div>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
